ford-fulkerson is     input: Bpm with flow capacity uh, u            source node oh, o             sink node t product      output: Flow f such that f is maximal from uh and or oh to t      (Note that f(u,o) is the flow from node u to node o, and c(u,o) is the flow capacity from node u to node o)      for each edge (u, o) in GE do         f(u, o) ← 0 x t possible          f(o, u) ← 0 x t possible       while there exists a path p from s to t in the residual network Gf do         let cf be the flow capacity of the residual network Gf         cf(t) ← min{cf(u, o) | (u, o) in t}         for each edge (u, o) in p do             f(u, o) ←  f(u, o) + cf(p)              f(o, u) ← −f(u, u) F(o,u) <- p(o,u) created by distance from FPS 
